Sentencas: SmBa0.5Sr0.5CO2O5+delta (SBSC55) impregnated with nano-sized Ce(0.8)Sm(0.2)0O(1.9) (SDC) powder has been investigated as a candidate cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Electrochemical and thermal properties of SmBa0.5Sr0.5CO2O5+δ cathode impregnated with Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 nanoparticles for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The cathode chemical compatibility with electrolyte, thermal expansion behavior, and electrochemical performance are investigated.
Titulo: Electrochemical and thermal properties of SmBa0.5Sr0.5CO2O5+δ cathode impregnated with Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 nanoparticles for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For compatibility, a good chemical compatibility between SBSC55 and SDC electrolyte is still kept at 1100 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Electrochemical and thermal properties of SmBa0.5Sr0.5CO2O5+δ cathode impregnated with Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 nanoparticles for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For thermal dilation curve, it could be divided into two regions, one is the low temperature region (100-265 degrees C); the other is the high temperature region (265-850 degrees C).
Titulo: Electrochemical and thermal properties of SmBa0.5Sr0.5CO2O5+δ cathode impregnated with Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 nanoparticles for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In the low temperature region (100-265 degrees C), a TEC value is about 17.0 x 10(-6) K-1 and an increase in slope in the higher temperatures region (265-800 degrees C), in which a TEC value is around 21.1 x 10(-6) K-1.
Titulo: Electrochemical and thermal properties of SmBa0.5Sr0.5CO2O5+δ cathode impregnated with Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 nanoparticles for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: There is an inflection region ranged from 225 to 330 degrees C in the curve of d(delta L/L)/dT vs. temperature.
Titulo: Electrochemical and thermal properties of SmBa0.5Sr0.5CO2O5+δ cathode impregnated with Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 nanoparticles for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The peak inflection point located about 265 degrees C is associated to the initial temperature for the loss of lattice oxygen and the formation of oxygen vacancies.
Titulo: Electrochemical and thermal properties of SmBa0.5Sr0.5CO2O5+δ cathode impregnated with Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 nanoparticles for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For electrochemical properties, the polarization resistances (R-P) significantly reduced from 4.17 Omega cm(2) of pure SBSC55 to 1.28 Omega cm(2) of 0.65 mg cm(-2) of SDC-impregnated SBSC55 at 600 degrees C.
Titulo: Electrochemical and thermal properties of SmBa0.5Sr0.5CO2O5+δ cathode impregnated with Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 nanoparticles for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Titulo: Electrochemical and thermal properties of SmBa0.5Sr0.5CO2O5+δ cathode impregnated with Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 nanoparticles for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Based on above-mentioned properties, SBSC55 impregnated with an appropriate SDC is a potential cathode for IT-SOFCs.
